title: Pacific Dogwood, after overnight rain
tags: pacificdogwood afterovernightrain gardenvillage burnaby britishcolumbia
description_content:
301/365,
The Pacific Dogwood. (Cornus Nuttallii) was adopted as British Columbia's provincial flower in 1956. Actually a flowering tree, the Pacific Dogwood is known for its white blooms, brilliant red berries and bright foliage in the fall.
 
Garden Village, Burnaby, British Columbia
